Israel Chemicals Rises Most in 2 Weeks as Potash Prices Climb

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-04-20T11:50:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/israel-chemicals-rises-most-in-2-weeks-as-potash-prices-climb.html
Israel Chemicals Ltd. (ICL) , which
extracts minerals from the  Dead Sea  to make fertilizer, rose the
most in more than two weeks as potash prices jumped.  The shares gained 3.1 percent, the most since April 4, to
61.58 shekels at 2:07 p.m. in Tel Aviv.  Canpotex, the largest potash exporter, sold 200,000 tonnes
of granular grade potash to Brazilian customers at $520 per
metric ton CFR for shipment in May and June 2011 and announced
$50 increase in Asia and other Latin American markets, Fertecon
Potash Report said April 20.  Editors: Peter Branton, Susan Lerner  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in Tel Aviv at 
 rgoodman9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  